<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3772981>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Alvania scabra (Philippi, 1844). A–C. Magnisi (Sicily), neotype, height 1.9 mm, with original label (Monterosato coll. MCZR-M-22162/N). D, E. Messina (Sicily) height 1.9 mm, with original labels (Monterosato coll. ex Granata-Grillo coll. MCZR-M-22227). F, G. Pantelleria Is. (Sicily), height 2.1 mm (BA); H. Punta de na Gall (Menorca, Baleares, Spain), 10 m depth, height 1.6 mm (JT and JDO). I–N. Salina Is. (Sicily), height 1.75 mm (I), 2.15 mm (J), 2.1 mm (K), 1.85 mm (L), 1.8 mm (M), 1.9 mm (N) (BA). O, P. Los Escullos, Cabo de Gata (Spain) height 2.35 mm (AN29. MNHN). Q, R. Cabo de Palos (Spain), height 2.4 mm (BA)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3772981/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3772985>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Alvania scabra (Philippi, 1844). A–C. Rissoa oranica Pallary, 1900, lectotype from Arzew, Oran (Algeria), height 2.25 mm, with original label (Monterosato coll. ex Pallary coll. MCZR-M-22059/L). D. Rissoa oranica Pallary, 1900, paralectotype from Arzew, Oran (Algeria), height 2.4 mm (Monterosato coll. ex Pallary coll. MCZR-M-22059/P). E. paralectotype, same locality, height 2.2 mm (Monterosato coll. ex Pallary coll. MCZR-M-22059/P). F. Rissoa oranica Pallary, 1900, original drawing by (Pallary, 1900: 322, pl. VII, fig. 4). G. Rissoa oranica Pallary, 1900, drawing by (Pallary, 1920: 50, fig. 20). H. paralectotype, same locality, height 2 mm (Monterosato coll. ex Pallary coll. MCZR-M-22059/P). I. paralectotype, same locality, height 1.825 mm (Monterosato coll. ex Pallary coll. MCZR-M-22059/P). J. paralectotype, same locality, height 1.625 mm (Monterosato coll. ex Pallary coll. MCZR-M-22059/P)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3772985/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3772987>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Distribution of Alvania scabra (Philippi, 1844), based on the material examined and checked literature data. Red dots, Recent records; blue dot, fossil records." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3772987/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3773011>
    dc:description "FIGURE 15. Alvania spp. (SEM). A–C. Alvania scabra (Philippi, 1844) neotype, Monterosato coll. MCZR-M-22162/N, Magnisi (Sicily), height 1.9 mm. A. Shell. B. Detail of the protoconch microsculpture, same specimen. B1. Detail of the protoconchteleoconch microsculpture, same specimen. C. Detail of the teleoconch microsculpture, same specimen. D–F. Alvania sculptilis (Monterosato, 1877), syntype numbered 3, Monterosato coll. ex Joly coll. MCZR-M-22162/S,Algiers (Algeria), height 1.9 mm. D. Shell. E. Detail of the protoconch microsculpture, same specimen. F. Detail of the teleoconch microsculpture, same specimen. G–I. Alvania sculptilis (Monterosato, 1877), Getares (Spain), height 2.25 mm (IN). G. Shell. H. Detail of the protoconch microsculpture, same specimen. I. Detail of the teleoconch microsculpture, same specimen" ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3773011/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3773017>
    dc:description "FIGURE 18. Alvania spp. drawing of external soft parts. A, B. Alvania scabra (Philippi, 1844), S. Giovanni Li Cuti, Catania, Sicily, 4 m depth (DS). C, D. Alvania scabra (Philippi, 1844), Los Escullos, Cabo de Gata, Spain, (AN29. MNHN), redrawn after a sketch by Serge Gofas (Malaga). E, F. Alvania sororcula (Granata-Grillo, 1877), S. Raineri, “Degassifica”, Messina, Sicily, 2–4 m depth (DS). G, H. Alvania scuderii Villari, 2017, Ganzirri, Messina, Sicily, 4–5 m depth (MZB)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3773017/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3772989>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. A–O. Alvania sculptilis (Monterosato, 1877). A–C. syntype numbered 1 from Algiers (Algeria), height 2.25 mm, with original labels (Monterosato coll ex Joly coll. MCZR-M-22162/S). D. syntype numbered 2 from Algiers (Algeria), height 2.1 mm (Monterosato coll ex Joly coll. MCZR-M-22162/S). E. syntype numbered 3 from Algiers (Algeria), height 1.9 mm (Monterosato coll ex Joly coll MCZR-M-22162/S). F. Getares nord (Spain), height 1.55 mm (IN). G–I. Alvania conspicua (Pallary, 1900), Arzew, Oran (Algeria), height 2.1 mm with original label (MCZR-M-30061). J, K. Algiers (Algeria) height 1.7 mm, with original label (Monterosato coll. MCZR-M-22250). L. Getares, Algeciras (Spain) 3–6 m depth, height 2.25 mm (IN). M. same locality (Spain) 3–6 m depth, height 2.15 mm (IN). N, O. Algiers (Algeria) height 1.73 mm (IN). P. Merelina sculptilis May, 1920, original drawing (May, 1920: 62, pl. XV, fig 15)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3772989/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

